Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.87,1:41:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能让那孩子被撞到\N{\rEN}I had to keep this boy from getting hit.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.51,1:41:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你冲到公车前去救一个孩子?\N{\rEN}You stepped in front of a bus to save a IittIe boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.51,1:41:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我别无选择\N{\rEN}I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.81,1:41:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须这样做\N{\rEN}I had to.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.89,1:42:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个…还好\N{\rEN}It's.... It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.30,1:42:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 不怎么好 - 不\N{\rEN}-It's not great. -No.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.20,1:42:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还好 不赖\N{\rEN}It's okay. It's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.07,1:42:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是这几年英文文学里最出色的一部\N{\rEN}It's not the most amazing piece of EngIish Iiterature in severaI years...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.61,1:42:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是…还好\N{\rEN}...but it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.01,1:42:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道…\N{\rEN}You know...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.45,1:42:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我还能接受"还好"\N{\rEN}...I think I'm fine with ''okay.''
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.95,1:42:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,书剩下的部分就没什么意义了\N{\rEN}It doesn't make sense with the rest of the book though.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.69,1:42:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我会重写剩下的\N{\rEN}No, not yet. I'II rewrite the rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.49,1:42:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的助理说 她会回到出版商那…\N{\rEN}My assistant said she'd go back to the pubIisher...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.03,1:42:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…再争取一些时间 - 为什么?\N{\rEN}-...and request more time. -Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.00,1:42:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道 但是很贴心\N{\rEN}Don't know. It's awfuIIy sweet though.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.86,1:42:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 你为何要重写这本书?\N{\rEN}No, why did you change the book?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.77,1:42:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多理由\N{\rEN}Lots of reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.50,1:42:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我意识到我不能那样做\N{\rEN}I reaIized I just couIdn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.54,1:42:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他是真实的?\N{\rEN}Because he's reaI?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.04,1:42:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为那是关于一个人…\N{\rEN}Because it's a book about a man...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.01,1:42:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不知道他会死去 然后死掉了\N{\rEN}...who doesn't know he's about to die and then dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.22,1:43:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果这个人知道他会死去 知道如何避免\N{\rEN}But if the man does know he's going to die and dies anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.12,1:43:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是坦然死去…\N{\rEN}...dies wiIIingIy, knowing he couId stop it, then....
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.39,1:43:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 这不是你要让他活下来那种人吗?\N{\rEN}I mean, isn't that the type of man you want to keep aIive?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.73,1:43:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈罗德咬了一口巴伐利亚糖曲奇…\N{\rEN}As Harold took a bite of Bavarian sugar cookie...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.77,1:43:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他最终感到好像一切都会好起来\N{\rEN}...he finally felt as if everything was going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.77,1:43:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时 当我们在恐惧 在绝望\N{\rEN}Sometimes, when we lose ourselves in fear and despair...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.54,1:43:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在日常琐事 在一成不变\N{\rEN}...in routine and constancy...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.05,1:43:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在无望 在悲剧面前迷失自我时\N{\rEN}...in hopelessness and tragedy...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.82,1:43:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以感谢上帝的巴伐利亚糖曲奇\N{\rEN}...we can thank God for Bavarian sugar cookies.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.12,1:43:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很幸运 当没有曲奇的时候…\N{\rEN}And fortunately, when there aren't any cookies...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.06,1:43:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们仍能在我们身上那只熟悉的手上…\N{\rEN}...we can still find reassurance in a familiar hand on our skin...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.13,1:43:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是一种爱的手势上…\N{\rEN}...or a kind and loving gesture...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.94,1:43:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是细心的鼓励上…\N{\rEN}...or a subtle encouragement...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.71,1:43:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是一个爱的拥抱上\N{\rEN}...or a loving embrace...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.31,1:44:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是温暖的安慰上安下心来\N{\rEN}...or an offer of comfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.92,1:44:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而忘掉医院的担架…\N{\rEN}Not to mention hospital gurneys...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.62,1:44:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有鼻帖…\N{\rEN}...and nose plugs...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.46,1:44:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有吃不饱的丹麦人…\N{\rEN}...and uneaten Danish...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.94,1:44:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有窃窃私语…\N{\rEN}...and soft-spoken secrets...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.97,1:44:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有芬达史崔特卡斯特吉他…\N{\rEN}...and Fender Stratocasters...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.48,1:44:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许还有偶尔一篇小说\N{\rEN}...and maybe the occasional piece of fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.25,1:44:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须记住所有这一切…\N{\rEN}And we must remember that all these things...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.75,1:44:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些我们认为仅仅是平日生活中点缀的\N{\rEN}...the nuances, the anomalies, the subtleties...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.12,1:44:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,微妙 奇异 算计\N{\rEN}...which we assume only accessorize our days...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.39,1:44:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的存在有着更伟大高尚的原因：\N{\rEN}...are, in fact, here for a much larger and nobler cause:
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.03,1:44:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是来救我们的命的\N{\rEN}They are here to save our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.87,1:44:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这想法看上去很古怪\N{\rEN}l know the idea seems strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.67,1:45:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我也知道这恰好就是真实的\N{\rEN}But l also know that it just so happens to be true.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.27,1:45:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是：\N{\rEN}And so it was:
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.91,1:45:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只手表救了哈罗德·克里克\N{\rEN}A wristwatch saved Harold Crick.

